name: Hongkong Garden Restaurant
address: Jl. Bypass Ngurah Rai Gg. Kertapura VIII No.8, Kesiman Kertalangu, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
One of the best Chinese food in town.

A great place for any kind of events such as meetings, wedding ceremony, birthday party, anniversary, gala dinner, product launching, etc.
Also a nice place for family dinner, or lunch on social gathering with friends

they have a lot of selection room for different capacity. Huge outdoor space, big hall, large meeting room, small meeting room, and also some small room equipped with karaoke facilities.

Not only the place was good, but their food is really delicious. one of the best chinese food in Bali. Few times of visit and trying different menu each time. The result? The taste is only good and very good. I never found bad one.

A lot of parking space.

Good service with friendly staff.

A chinese restaurant with good food, good space and good service.
review 2: The foods are delicious. Maybe they need to consider the order of food served and during the day for lunch it a bit hot. It is good place for big weeding and group party. They have huge parking area and big entrance. The staffs are kind and polite.
review 3:
Big restourant with ballroom.. Capacity until 2000 people with round table & personal chair..

The food is funtastic delicious..
Many event using that place.. Like Fashion show, wedding ceremonial, etc..

Keep going this service..
review 4: Its a beautiful hall and garden but prepare to be disappointed: the food is not real chinese though the staff say it is. Very expensive for the average/low quality food.
review 5: The food is always delicious. The parking area is quite big and the security persons always organize each vehicles very well. Suitable for birthday party, wedding party or any kind of gatherings. This place is famous here.

name: Puri Nusa Indah Hotel
address: Jl. Waribang No.99, Kesiman Petilan, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: This is a hotel that I think has many memories. In middle school, my friends and I went on vacation to Bali and stayed here. lots of things to do here. You can have fun, play, even be sad at this hotel. In my opinion, this hotel's service is very good. The hotel staff are also friendly. But it's just that the rooms are a bit lacking. Over all it was comfortable, but the shower in my bathroom was broken. When I use, it only turns on in hot water. when I turn, it gets hotter. So my body was a bit hot when using it at that time. The food is delicious, there is a swimming pool too. But it's a bit of a miss, the location is far from destination and minimarkets. So when I'm hungry and want a snack other than hotel food, it's hard to find it. Apart from that, I don't have any problems with it. a quite comfortable and nice to live in. I hope you also have sweet memories at this hotel. thank you!
review 2: ....provide comfort and cleanliness budget hotel to meet your needs. Spacious parking, nice staffs. Meeting rooms also available, but just out of downtown or city center, so prepare your logistic properly. Good for group and meeting...
review 3: Broken closet but clean, water plenty but no hot shower. However totaly very cheap, enough parking lots for 5 buses, the standard comes with two big king size beds fits for 4. And airconned too
review 4: I'm here just for an workshop. Ao I don't know about the room. But the meeting room looks great. I hope the AC will be cooler. It will make it more comfortable.üëçüëç
review 5: Lack of wifi, hot water need some time to get out. Bed is average. No elevator at all.

name: Barong Dance Uma Dewi
address: Jl. Waribang No.21, Kesiman Petilan, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Really disappointed. Don‚Äôt waste your money and time watching this performance. It costs IDR 150k, the performers were not professional at all. They were chit chatting and laughing on the stage among themselves while performing.
You will never understand the story because their act is really bad even though you got a summary of the story in English. Go do something else instead of coming here‚Ä¶ seriously
review 2:
This is not for kids at all, the jokes they used is 17+. You will not get the story even though they give you the storyline paper. If you searching for traditional and cultural experience, this place is not going to give you any of it. The actual story is only 10-15 minutes but because they put a lot of unnecessary jokes and interactions this takes longer (about 1 hour).
After that, they might offer photos together with actors, but i recommend to DO NOT take any photo with them. They ask for money after taking the photo (not beforehand). They asked for a certain amount of money (for me it is too much) and they charged per person. So if you take a group photo, you all have to pay (mine was IDR 20K per person). Few of them not charging a lot (IDR 2K or 5K) is fine.
review 3: Traditional dance with a bit of drama and comedy. Was a little awkward the comedy part to see with kids. While taking photos Barong secretly asked for money. That was a bit unprofessional. Ticketed show so already paid for it before entering.
review 4: Such a fun experience! A beautiful dance and the story of it is so meaningful with talented dancer and traditional music player.
review 5:
Don't waste your time and money. Such a boring dance and you've to pay IDR 100K for entrance which is super expensive. The pace of the whole act is super slow and they just drag a 10 min show to 1 hour.

Just an trap to make some money from the tourist. The photo might looks good but trust me you can't even bear it for 5 min so please avoid this place.

name: Sekopi.Bypass
address: JL. By Pass Ngurah Rai No.88B, Sanur Kaja, Denpasar Selatan, Kesiman, East Denpasar, Denpasar City, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: The cafe is situated just off the highway with ample parking space. It is very beautifully decorated. The coffee tasted strong and delicious. The staff members are very polite and attentive. I loved this place!
review 2: It is good but it is not cozy as much as the one in Renon
review 3: Very big parking, coffee was good, very affordable. Food was surprisingly tasty but need to add a bit of veggies.
review 4: Basketball court and coffee shop in one place.
review 5: I have experience in hospitality. Don't ever tell your customer to move to another table, if it‚Äôs reserved in the first place let them know earlier. It doesn‚Äôt matter how much money your customer spend coz they are the one who help you to keep your business running

name: Buana Mas Resto
address: Jl. Waribang No.28x, Kesiman Petilan, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Very nice restaurant, has the feel of an old Balinese building, very shady and beautiful, large parking area.
Very tasty food, very good service, very friendly staff. Prices are very affordable.
This restaurant is very good for groups or families.
It has many restrooms. There is also a prayer room.
All areas are kept clean
review 2:
The place is very quiet and homey. They provide a buffet menu, but it doesn't suit my taste buds.
The place is very clean and has lots of green plants, the toilets are also many and clean at a rate of Rp. 2000
review 4: Old but gold place for eating. Traditional vibes

name: Umakami Resto
address: Jl. Waribang No.88a, Kesiman Petilan, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: It is a very lovely caf√© and restaurants whit amazing view, also many tables have electricity access and since it is quite, it is a good place to work.
review 2: Best meal in Bali! Food selection, food quality, price, service, location; all perfect! We had entrees, mains and desserts, and drinks. Overlooking a rice field, quiet seating area out back, beautiful staff. We will be back.
review 3:
Very bright place and amazing food. We like Pork-Star bit this is better!!!
Poker Belly Sambal Matah was our favourite!
review 4:
Been here view times,
The thing I like most about this cafe is "RISOLES" my favorite menu.
And for the coffee, it's okay if you are not a coffee addict. But if you like sweet coffee, maybe coffee with gula aren, (forgot the name). But the recommended time to come here is early in the morning or afternoon.
review 5: Umakami is a hidden gem situated in the denpasar area. Surrounded by their own plantation with very friendly service and amazing food and drinks. Above all the price is very affordable, highly recommend this restaurant.

name: Hare Krisna Vegetarian
address: 87W2+8M4, Jl. Waribang, Kesiman, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: If you are a vegetarian and looking for simple food, Hare Krisna vegetarian is the right place. The lady who runs it is very smile. She made her own vegetarian nasi campur and bakso. The price is also very afordable. The taste of the food is unlike vegetarian in Jakarta. I can say that the "dendeng" is awesome. The place is very simple and quiet.
review 2:
Food is delicious. All with vegetarian food with Balinese flavour.
Staffs are helpful and explain the food . Little difficulty is that no airconditioner or fan.
If weather is hot , have to bear it for the good food.
review 3: Good vegan food,  amazing prices. Yummy donuts with chocolate sprinkles 2,000IDR. Definitely recommend the vegan bakso (Indonesian 'meatball' soup). Small portions, but just means you can try more dishes.
review 4: The most amazing Balinese taste vegetarian/vegan dishes i ever try.. Polite staff and beautiful environment.. I really love the food and the garden.. I hope there's a improvement on detail, like bathroom lights.. But overall i gonna be back again and again and again.
review 5:
Not bad, definitely not too used to the local critters dining with us (ants were covering the floor with cats and other small creatures).

Food wise they operate by a vegetarian philosophy, with no byproducts created by harming animals.

We ordered the Mi goreng and the premade spring roll and deep fried banana. Luckily we use Google translate to get a rough translation. With a cold Spring water, it came down to about 40k RP.

The food was decent, a tad spicy for my tastes and the banana was a little stale. Mind you we arrived at 430 pm, which is when they close. Overall though was a nice experience and happy to find another cheap, friendly, vegetarian warung!

review 3: The taste is okay, the satay isn't good enough
review 4: The shop has been around for many years. Lawar chicken, pork and beef. 35k a portion. It is a must try!!!
review 5: Good local food. Selling pork, beef and chicken. The taste is still authentic.  Love it

name: Sekaa Barong Eka Budhi
address: Jl. Waribang No.11, Kesiman Petilan, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Best barong performance!
I always bring my tourist groups here! The owner is also very kind and frendly. He allows us to visit his family temple which seems to be very old and interesting!
He even provides visitors with explanation about Balinese Hinduism!
Thank you mr Ida Bagus!
review 2:
Traditional barony show, they perform once a day 9:30-10:30
Even the dialogue is presented in Balinese, the performance is worth to watch.
review 3:
It's a play expressing indonesia culture, story, act and feelings. This play consists of 5 stories overall on the day we visited. Almost play is for 1.5 hours and entrance fee costed 10000 rupiye for each person. They play live music and each characters performance is based on stories.
And the entire play is based on barong and Kris dance. They believe barong as the powerful lion which comes and help them from all difficulties.
review 4:
An hour long performance of the traditional Balinese Dance form - Barong Dance. The dance is performed over the beats and music of traditional percussion drums and flutes, with actors decked in traditional ceremonial outfits enacting various roles. The dance itself is divides into 5 acts, telling the story of the fight between good and evil through mythical characters, animals and creatures.
Good one time experience.
review 5: It is a comedy Bali culture dance.. The acting is so bad.. It is only just a little bit of the girl dance and that all.. A totally waste of time.. Was introduced by the driver.. I think they all get commissions for it. Would not recommend at all.
